  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Analyzing Design Requirements**\n\nI\'m currently dissecting the images and design system description to establish a solid understanding of the project\'s visual and functional needs. My focus is on identifying key elements, patterns, and interactive components. The goal is to define the required features. I\'m prioritizing accuracy and clarity.\n\n\n**Defining Visual Direction**\n\nI\'ve been immersed in the \"Silk & Stone\" and \"Atmosfera PAME\" aesthetic, focusing on the \"Silk Neomorphism\" principles. I\'m noting the soft, off-white/pinkish backgrounds and subtle neomorphic shadows, as well as the deep purple primary color palette. I\'ve begun to define the elements for the two pathways present in the welcome screen, and am beginning to map the content for the user triage form.\n\n\n**Structuring User Interactions**\n\nNow, I\'m focusing on the user triage form\'s structure. I\'m noting the progression from questions about the last deep clean, to room dimensions (with +/- counters), and surfaces needing specific care. The final step is defining desired cleaning frequency via radio options, all leading to the pricing page. The pricing page includes a sidebar for seamless navigation.\n\n\n**Developing Pricing Structures**\n\nI\'m now deep-diving into the mobile app\'s pricing matrix design, specifically the \"Matriz de Investimento\" content section. I\'m focusing on \"Meio Turno\" (4h) and \"Turno Completo\" (9h) options. I\'m noting the distinction between \"Sess\303\243o Avulsa\" and \"Pacote Mensal\" offers, including the monthly savings for each. The \"Turno Completo\" package will be highlighted as the \"A ESCOLHA INTELIGENTE\". I plan to integrate interactive elements allowing real-time price calculation based on user selections and add-on services. This includes add-ons like \"Dobra T\303\251cnica\", \"Passadoria de Autor\" and \"Polimento de Metais\", all at R$ 50 each.\n\n\n**Formulating Recruitment Logic**\n\nI\'m now focusing on the recruitment form, specifically its structure and functionality. I\'m noting the split layout, the form fields (name, birthdate, experience, references, criminal record), and the \"SUBMETER TRIAGE\" submission button. I\'m also considering the user\'s HTML image integration request. I am exploring the possibility of directly linking the app to the images from the HTML, which should allow for a more streamlined user experience. I am examining the source URL for the logo, both in white on purple and transparent variants.\n\n\n**Extracting Image URLs**\n\nI\'m now extracting and verifying image URLs for the welcome screen backgrounds and the central badge (logo). I\'ve confirmed URLs for both the left and right backgrounds and the logo with a purple background. I\'m prioritizing their integration into the design flow. This should enable us to create the final UI with minimal friction.\n\n\n**Integrating Image URLs**\n\nI\'ve extracted the image URL for the recruitment screen\'s left-side content. I\'m focusing on incorporating it within the recruitment screen design to enhance visual appeal. I\'m prioritizing ensuring the image is displayed correctly and optimally on the recruitment page.\n\n\n"
    modified_response: "I will start by reviewing the `package.json` and `metadata.json` files to check the project setup, dependencies, and metadata configuration. This ensures that we configure the app correctly and give it an elegant, descriptive title."
    thinking_duration {
