    thinking: "**Considering App Code Design**\n\nI\'m now diving into the app\'s code structure. My focus is on modularity, inspired by guidelines emphasizing distinct modules to avoid monolithic files. Specifically, I am actively preventing the creation of a single file for all the logic. I want to build a flexible and easy to maintain app.\n\n\n**Structuring App Code Components**\n\nI\'m now implementing the modular code split. I\'m actively establishing `/src/types.ts` for defining crucial interfaces. Also, I\'m constructing `/src/data.ts` to manage static data. In addition, I am creating several components: `/src/components/Sidebar.tsx`, `/src/components/Header.tsx`, `/src/components/WelcomeScreen.tsx` and `/src/components/ClientTriage.tsx` for a structured and easily understandable structure.\n\n\n**Defining App Component States**\n\nI\'m now detailing the app\'s internal states. I\'ve realized I need to track the active screen for easy user navigation. I\'m thinking about defining the screens as `\"welcome\"`, `\"triage\"`, `\"pricing\"`, and `\"recruitment\"`. I\'m also considering direct sidebar navigation for the `\"pricing\"` screen or a general nav that allows going to home. Next, I\'m working on the components: `/src/components/PricingMatrix.tsx` for the bento-grid investment matrix, including interactive sliders/counters for price estimation and `/src/components/RecruitmentForm.tsx`, mirroring a specific image with file upload support.\n\n\n"
    modified_response: "I will create `/src/types.ts` to hold variables, interfaces, and state representations. This will keep the codebase modular, avoiding type pollution and infinite re-render bugs."
